<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Two options to deal with the obnoxious -PvP</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:13 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Two options to deal with the obnoxious -PvP<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=451" TARGET=_self>We need more PvP options</A> (Conin_app_BCK)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>First option is to play on the PvP only server where everyone is red. Now you don't have the problem of not being able to deal with th eoffending party.
<P>Second option is to use the /ignore feature so you never have to listen to them again.
<P>&gt; I'm sure this has happened to you before: You are talking
<BR>&gt; somewhere about something and a certian person likes to butt in
<BR>&gt; and let you know what they think. You have conflicting of views,
<BR>&gt; and you'd like to show him a thing or two especially because he
<BR>&gt; is 5 or so levels below you, but alas either he is not PvP, or
<BR>&gt; you aren't PvP or both. And there is no way he would /duel you
<BR>&gt; because he's afraid of you.
<P>&gt; So what do you do? many of you have played uo and i know a lot
<BR>&gt; of you want to scream when i mention it, but things were so
<BR>&gt; easy! you could just take them down, or get your buddies on him.
<BR>&gt; Wasn't that fun? there has to be some way we can do that,
<BR>&gt; without the antagonist purposly bugging people and he knows
<BR>&gt; there isn't a thing you can do about it-ha ha! I really like
<BR>&gt; Theblack's idea but what about the buggers who know they are
<BR>&gt; safe because they aren't pvp?
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
